<p>We&#8217;re hoping that with this release, users will no longer see a barrier, and more users will be willing to try their hands at custom add-on development.</p>

<h2>The Docs</h2>

<p>After the new add-on manager in <a href="https://docs.expressionengine.com/v3/about/changelog.html#id45">ExpressionEngine 3</a> there was no longer a division in add-on types (plugins, extensions, fieldtypes, modules, etc), everything was listed one page. Likewise, installing add-ons became easier with the <code>addon.setup.php</code> file. However, despite all the changes, the docs have always reflected a mix of the old and the new. Today, we&#8217;re changing that.</p>

