				<h3>Entry Cloning</h3>

<p>Today we&#8217;re happy to announce the VERY often requested addition of entry cloning as part of ExpressionEngine Pro 1.2.</p>

<p>Check out the following 1 minute video to see it in action!</p>

<iframe width="600" height="360" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/cSz7NZdQvGk?rel=0" title="YouTube video player" frameborder="0" allow="accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture" allowfullscreen></iframe>

<h3>How To Clone Channel Entries</h3>

<p>To clone an entry, open the original entry from the Entry Manager. Then click Save -> Clone to New Entry.</p>

<figure>
    <center><img src="https://expressionengine.com/asset/img/blog/clone_to_new_entry.png" alt="Clone to New Entry"></center>
</figure>

<p>You will then be redirected to the new entry. Note that the new entry will have a status of Closed, and the Title will automatically be prefixed with “Copy of” to prevent confusion with your original entry.</p>

<p>Take a peek at the full <a href="https://docs.expressionengine.com/latest/installation/changelog.html">change log</a>!</p>

<p><em>Please note, we consider this phase 1 of entry cloning, while we already have plans in place for phase 2 we&#8217;re eager to hear your feedback to help us shape those plans further!</em></p>

