				";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:2:"en";s:5:"child";a:1:{s:27:"http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom";a:2:{s:4:"name";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:10:"Tom Jaeger";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:2:"en";}}s:5:"email";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:18:"Tom@PacketTide.com";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:2:"en";}}}}}}s:8:"category";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:0:"";s:7:"attribs";a:1:{s:0:"";a:3:{s:4:"term";s:17:"CP Accessory Feed";s:6:"scheme";s:60:"https://expressionengine.com/blog/category/cp-accessory-feed";s:5:"label";s:17:"CP Accessory Feed";}}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:2:"en";}}s:7:"content";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:2429:"
				<p>Today we&#8217;re excited to announce the release of ExpressionEngine 6.2 as well as Pro 1.1!</p>

<p>ExpressionEngine 6.2 has oodles of new additions, fixes, and updates that fall under two main themes.</p>

<h2>Security</h2>

<p>The first is security.  As mentioned in our <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=QpeygAbaR-0">update video last month</a>, this release is being flagged as a <strong>critical security update.</strong>  Please note this <strong>is not due to a specific critical security bug</strong> that has been fixed, but due to the sheer number of lower severity security items that have been addressed since the initial 6.0.0 release.</p>

<p>ExpressionEngine has long been known for its security, as such, we felt it was time to take a step forward with password requirements, in 6.2.0 we&#8217;re also rolling out a new <a href="https://docs.expressionengine.com/latest/control-panel/settings/security-privacy.html#password-security-policy">Password Security Policy</a>.  Please note, if you previously had &#8220;Require Secure Passwords&#8221; set, this is now considered the &#8220;Basic&#8221; password policy.</p>

<figure>
    <img src="https://expressionengine.com/asset/img/blog/pw-validation.png" alt="Password Security Policy in Action">
</figure>

<p>In addition to the new Password Security Policy, we&#8217;ve also added Multi-Factor Authentication to Pro 1.1.</p>

<figure>
    <center><img src="https://expressionengine.com/asset/img/blog/mfa.png" alt="Multi Factor Authentication"></center>
</figure>

<h2>Additional Features</h2>

<p>In addition to security, we decided to take the opportunity to sprinkle in roughly 20+ additional feature requests from the community.  While we encourage you to take a peek at the full <a href="https://docs.expressionengine.com/latest/installation/changelog.html">change log</a>, the following are a few noteworthy changes to call out!</p>

<ul>
<li>Ability to view password on login</li>
<li>Ability to search by url_title and entry_id in entries manager</li>
<li>New channel entries parameters</li>
<li>Improved search performance (<a href="https://github.com/ExpressionEngine/ExpressionEngine/pull/1410">Hat tip to Robson</a>)</li>
<li>Improve cookie registration</li>
<li>Performance enhancements</li>
<li>PHP 8.1 Support</li>
<li><a href="https://docs.expressionengine.com/latest/installation/changelog.html">Many more</a></li>
</ul>

